title: Grateful Dead Live at Sam Boyd Silver Bowl on 1991-04-27

reviews.review_text: Lost Wages  This was a fun show , maybe because of the huge contingent from Tucson that made the road trip , either flying or driving . A solid set list , very well played , almost a greatest hits list . The weather was nice , low 80's , outdoors no humidity ..... and after the show , the Huns invaded Vegas and it was tie dyes everywhere on the strip .
